thread.title: G20 weighed down by free trade negotiations

title: G20 weighed down by free trade negotiations
text:
G20 weighed down by free trade negotiations Tuesday, March 20, 2018 - 01:51 
World financial leaders gathered at the G20 summit in Buenos Aires are searching for an endorsement of free trade amid worries about U.S. metals tariffs and looming trade sanctions on China, but Trump administration officials said they won't sacrifice U.S. national interests. Kate King reports.
